<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36216b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36216b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36216b"> 216(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Flaundrish hat</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Some concerned New Amsterdammers]</font> accused the old governor of being highly aristocratical; and in truth there seems to have been some ground for such an accusation; for he carried himself with a lofty, soldier-like air, and was somewhat particular in dress, appearing, when not in uniform, in rich apparel of the antique <mark>flaundrish cut</mark>. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 346</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
